post_text:
School Bus Information!

Drivers are excited to be driving regular routes and transporting students again! We do ask that during the first week of classes, families arrive at their bus stop early and show flexibility. Routes typically run a little slower since drivers will be taking extra care to make sure stops are not missed and that our students, especially the youngest, are safely seated, understand the rules, and get on and off at the correct stops.

Please make sure your child understands that if s/he is uncertain about a stop they should not get off the bus. Tell your child to communicate with the driver their concerns.

Younger children (Preschool and Kindergarten) cannot leave the bus unless an adult is there to meet them. If an adult is not present, the driver will return to school with that student. Please be aware and make necessary accommodations as the Preschool and Kindergarten mid-day routes will not begin until September 8th, 2020.

Questions or concerns regarding bussing please contact the Transportation Director 208.934.4321 ext. 3380

post_text: Parents, as you register you will notice a question that asks about your current living situation. It's not just because our counselors are being nosy. If a family is living with another family or staying in an RV, due to a financial hardship, our counselors want to reach out and offer resources. This information also helped our school qualify for free lunches in our elementary school. This information is only seen by our school counselors and is confidential. Thank you! If you should have further questions please reach out to one of the counselors.

Gooding School District is finalizing plans to open school as traditionally as possible as scheduled on August 24th, with increased safety precautions around COVID.

The Gooding School District approved a plan at the July 14th board meeting, and the district will continue to finalize details prior to the start of school. The district will continually update the community on details as the start of school draws near. The plan is located at https://www.goodingschools.org/images/stories/Resources/SchoolBoard/AgendaItems/2020-July/GSD_Reopening-Closure_Protocol.pdf

However, we do realize for some families traditional school is not the best option. Our hope is that we can provide our students and families with a great home school option. If you are interested in a home school option please complete the following survey.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf8dcRzFzLjaKJYPf0dMAAMSYhZaxIEkwpQaadU8lCSrZLclw/viewform?usp=sf_link

shared_text:
Idaho PTV Teachers
May 26 at 9:30 PM ¬∑

Samantha Knittle from Gooding Elementary School in the Gooding School District, along with her scurvy friend, Pirate Pat, are teaching 4th graders this week on #ClassroomIdaho on Idaho Public Television. Be sure to check them out on our Create channel or YouTube!

Samantha (Sam) Knittle is a 4th grade teacher at Gooding Elementary School. She has a degree in civil engineering and architecture from Washington State University. It was not until after graduation, that she realize wearing fairy wings to reinforced concrete lectures was a sign she should have been an elementary school teacher instead. If you had told her in college that someday she would live in a small town, surrounded by cows and corn, in Southern Idaho she would have laughed at you. However, Sam absolutely loves her students, cows, husband, and being able to bike everywhere in town!

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLvDo4LDXnoaD4YqdEYHDs7U_O33X6_v7h

Graduation reminder:
Seating for tonight's graduation is limited to eight (8) people per graduate, and the group must arrive together. Parking in the football complex will be only be available for elderly family members and family members who have a handicap. Parking for those family members will be along the outside of the visitor fencing with the front of the car facing the football field. All others vehicles will need to be parked in the high school parking lot. Remember, seating will begin at 6:00 pm and seats are not provided.

The Board of Trustees voted to move forward with the Graduation Plan!
Graduation for 2020 will be held on Tuesday, May 26th at 7:00 PM and will be held on the football field, and graduates will be seated on the home bleachers. The field will be marked into grids for family members but is limited to eight (8) members per family in order for some social distancing to occur. Grid positions were determined in a random drawing with seniors and Mr. Patterson. Graduates will meet behind the school. All other family members must arrive together to be seated in the assigned grid and will need to provide seating for themselves. Please note that once someone leaves the area, he or she will not be able to return. Seating will begin at 6:00, with assistance provided by staff and Board members. The decision to allow vehicles into the complex will be made on Tuesday, as the ground will need to be dry. If you are sick or at-risk of getting sick, please do not attend. The ceremony will be streamed live on Gooding High School‚Äôs Facebook page.

Congratulations class of 2020!!!

post_text:
From the Superintendent...

Typically administration creates graduation plans. However, during this unique time, administration felt the Board should be included. At the last board meeting, trustees approved a graduation plan on the football field. The approval was contingent upon insurance liability concerns needing to be resolved regarding Covid-19 and also legal concerns for the use of a release of liability waiver. I reached out to the insurance company and the district's attorney, and those findings will be presented at a special board meeting on Wednesday. The Board's decision is currently in effect. Graduation plans may or may not change at Wednesday's board meeting. If you have questions, please direct them to administration.

Thank you, Mr. Larsen

Families here you will find learning resources for your kindergarten through fifth grade child for the week of April 13th.
